1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,210
Make this test sometime soon.

2
00:00:02,320 --> 00:00:06,929
Propose one of these ideas to someone and then watch his behavior.

3
00:00:06,929 --> 00:00:08,370
1.

4
00:00:08,560 --> 00:00:14,610
The postal system, long a government monopoly, should be turned over to private enterprise.

5
00:00:14,610 --> 00:00:15,650
2.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:21,650
Presidential elections should be held every two or six years instead of four.

7
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:22,929
3.

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:32,689
Regular hours for retail stores should be 1 p.m. to 8 p.m. instead of 9 a.m. to 5.30 p.m. 4.

9
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:36,370
The retirement age should be raised to 70.

10
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:41,169
Whether these ideas are sound or practical is not the point.

11
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:45,809
What is significant is how a person handles propositions like these.

12
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:49,809
If he laughs at the idea and doesn't give it a second thought,

13
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:56,530
and probably 95% will laugh at it, chances are he suffers from tradition paralysis.

14
00:00:56,640 --> 00:01:01,730
But the one in 20 who says, that's an interesting idea, tell me more about it,

15
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,929
has a mind that's turned to creativity.

16
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:13,169
Traditional thinking is personal enemy number one for the person who is interested in a creative personal success program.

17
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:20,370
Traditional thinking freezes your mind, blocks your progress, and prevents you from developing creative power.

18
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:22,929
Here are three ways to fight it.

19
00:01:22,929 --> 00:01:24,049
1.

20
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,530
Become receptive to ideas.

21
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,290
Welcome new ideas.

22
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:30,850
Destroy these thought repellents.

23
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:31,890
Won't work.

24
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,010
Can't be done.

25
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:36,049
It's useless, and it's stupid.

26
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:43,010
A very successful friend of mine who holds a major position with an insurance company said to me,

27
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:50,530
I don't pretend to be the smartest guy in the business, but I think I am the best sponge in the insurance industry.

28
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:54,770
I make it a point to soak up all the good ideas I can.

29
00:01:54,770 --> 00:01:56,770
2.

30
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,169
Be an experimental person.

31
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:01,410
Break up fixed routines.

32
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:06,770
Expose yourself to new restaurants, new books, new theaters, new friends.

33
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,169
Take a different route to work someday.

34
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,490
Take a different vacation this year.

35
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,290
Do something new and different this weekend.

36
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:22,689
If your work is in distribution, develop an interest in production, accounting, finance, and the other elements of business.

37
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:27,329
This gives you breadth and prepares you for larger responsibilities.

38
00:02:27,329 --> 00:02:28,610
3.

39
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:31,569
Be progressive, not regressive.

40
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:34,770
Not, that's the way we did it where I used to work,

41
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:41,250
so we ought to do it that way here, but, how can we do it better than we did it where I used to work?

42
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:46,130
not backward regressive thinking, but forward progressive thinking.

